<MyH2 text="Essential Gear for Salmon Fishing" />
<MyH3 text="Rods and Reels" />
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Rod:</strong> Medium-heavy 8'6" to 10'6"
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Reel:</strong> Baitcasting or level-wind with a strong drag system
    </li>
</ul>
<MyH3 text="Line and Leaders" />
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Main Line:</strong> 30–40 lb braided
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Leader:</strong> 20–25 lb fluorocarbon
    </li>
</ul>
<MyH3 text="Lures and Bait" />
<ul>
    <li>
        Spinners (Blue Fox, Mepps)
    </li>
    <li>
        Herring (fresh or plug-cut)
    </li>
    <li>
        Salmon eggs or roe
    </li>
    <li>
        Kwikfish or Flatfish plugs
    </li>
</ul>
<MyH2 text="Bank Fishing vs Boat Fishing" />
<MyH3 text="Bank Fishing Pros:" />
<ul>
    <li>
        Low cost
    </li>
    <li>
        Easy access in places like Sandy or Clackamas Rivers
    </li>
</ul>
<MyH3 text="Boat Fishing Pros:" />
<ul>
    <li>
        Greater reach
    </li>
    <li>
        Ideal for trolling on big waters like the Columbia
    </li>
</ul>
<p class="mb-4">
    Choose based on your budget, experience, and comfort level.
</p>
