<MyH2 text="FAQs About Salmon Fishing Near Portland" />
<MyH3 text="1. Do I need a boat to catch salmon near Portland?" />
<p class="mb-4">
    No, many rivers like the Sandy and Clackamas offer excellent bank access. However, boats are ideal for larger bodies like the Columbia.
</p>
<MyH3 text="2. What’s the best time of year to catch salmon near Portland?" />
<p class="mb-4">
    Late spring (April–May) and fall (September–October) are the most productive times, depending on the salmon run.
</p>
<MyH3 text="3. Can I fish for salmon with kids?" />
<p class="mb-4">
    Absolutely! Many spots like Barton Park and Sauvie Island are family-friendly and safe for young anglers.
</p>
<MyH3 text="4. Are there fishing guides near Portland?" />
<p class="mb-4">
    Yes, numerous professional guides operate out of Portland and nearby coastal towns like Tillamook and Nehalem.
</p>
<MyH3 text="5. What bait works best for salmon in Oregon?" />
<p class="mb-4">
    Fresh herring, cured salmon eggs, and spinners are all effective. Choice depends on the river and time of year.
</p>
<MyH3 text="6. How do I get an Oregon fishing license?" />
<p class="mb-4">
    You can purchase a license online at <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://myodfw.com/">myodfw.com</a>, or at local fishing and sporting goods stores.
</p>
